    %h4 Travel
    %a{:href=>"http://www.coxconventioncenter.com/maps/images/popmap3.jpg"}
      %img{:src=>"http://www.coxconventioncenter.com/maps/images/popmap3.jpg",:class=>"right",:width=>125}

    %p Oklahoma City is conveniently located in both the center of the midwest and the nation itself, making it an ideal location for a conference. Our city is within a days drive from Dallas, Kansas City, Austin, Saint Louis, Memphis, Albuquerque, and Denver. Convenient direct flights from cities on both coasts are available to the <a href="http://www.flyokc.com/">Will Rogers World Airport</a>. By Car, the Cox Convention Center is conveniently accessible off of I-40 and I-35.</a>.

    .spacer.clear

    %h4 Downtown Oklahoma City

    %p Oklahoma City has a thriving downtown with many hotels, restaurants, nightclubs, museums and parks. There numerous <A href="http://www.okccvb.org/index.php?submenu=what_to_do&src=gendocs&ref=WhattoDo&category=Main">activities</a> and <a href="http://www.okccvb.org/index.php?submenu=where_to_stay_dt&xsearch[0]=Downtown&submit.x=7&submit.y=6&submit=Go&xsearch_id=partners_search_hotel_area&src=directory&view=partners_lister_hotels&submenu=where_to_stay_dt">amenities</a> suitable for business, pleasure or a mix of both.   

 

